    43→
    44→	Use-cases:
    45→	1. Parse JSON via the [`bourne` package](https://github.com/hapijs/bourne) to protect from prototype pollution.
    46→	2. Parse JSON with [`reviver` option of `JSON.parse()`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/parse).
    47→
    48→	@default JSON.parse()
    49→
    50→	@example
    51→	```
    52→	import ky from 'ky';
    53→	import bourne from '@hapijs/bourne';
    54→
    55→	const json = await ky('https://example.com', {
    56→		parseJson: text => bourne(text)
    57→	}).json();
